<!--START TYPING CONTENT FOR SESSION BELOW HERE-->
<worksheet>
  <title>Getting Warmed Up and In the Right Mindset</title>
  <exercise workspace="1 in">
    <statement>
      <p>
        A bag contains the same size marbles in three different colors: red, blue, and white. The bag has 14 identical 
        red marbles, 12 identical blue marbles, and 20 identical white marbles (all the same size).  
        One marble is drawn from the bag and the color of the marble is noted. Let <m>B</m> be the event the marble drawn is 
        blue, <m>R</m> the event the marble drawn is red, and W the event the marble drawn is white.
      </p>
    </statement>
  </exercise>
  
</worksheet>

<worksheet>
 <title>Let's Get Our Hands On</title> 
 <image width="20%">
    <shortdescription>
      This is an image
    </shortdescription>
    <latex-image>
      \begin{tikzpicture}
        \draw (0,0) rectangle (1,1);
      \end{tikzpicture}
    </latex-image>
  </image>
    <exercise workspace="1 in">
      <statement>
        <p>
          Explain the meaning of <m>\displaystyle\lim_{x \to 3} f(x) = -2</m>.
        </p>
      </statement>
    </exercise>  
</worksheet>
  
<worksheet>
 <title>Now Grades Go Up</title> 
 <exercise workspace ="1 in">
  <statement>
    <p>
      The mathematical notation <m>\displaystyle\lim \limits_{x \rightarrow 5} f(x)</m> means <m>\underline{ \qquad\qquad}</m>
        <ol marker="(a)">
          <li> <p>we need to find the value of the function  at <m>x=5</m>.</p> </li>
          <li> <p> we need to investigate the <m>y</m>-values of <m>f(x)</m> as <m>x</m> gets very near <m>x=5</m> from both the left and right sides of <m>x=5</m>, 
            but not necessarily at <m>x=5</m>.</p> </li>
          <li> <p>we need to find the horizontal asymptotes. </p> </li>
          <li> <p> we need to find the instantaneous rate of change.</p> </li>
          <li> <p> we need to investigate the <m>y</m>-values as we approach <m>x=5</m> only on the right side.</p> </li>
        </ol>
    </p>
  </statement>
 </exercise>
</worksheet>

